Bass fishing is the best though  Best Tournament Position: Tied 12th on Sparrow and 17th overall with  4 out of 5 events fished in BM100 league.  # of Tournament seasons:  2, with many many more to come.  Sponsors: None  Spouse: None.....come on I'm only 20  Children: 3.........kidding  Most importantly  Pet peeve: People with no fishing/boating etiquette, which you can rant about all you want on these boards, but no matter what, the people that have this issue aren't the one on these boards. Name: Steve Rowbotham  DOB: 23/12/1986  Home Town: Barrie  Schooling: Fish and Wildlife Technology  Home Lake: Lake Simcoe/Couchiching  Funny Fact: I spend more time sharpening lures than doing college homework.  Boat: 2002 Legend XCalibur 179 with 75HP Mercury 4-Stroke  Big Fish: Largemouth - 6lbs 7oz (Sparrow Lake) Smallmouth - 6lbs 4oz (Lake Couchiching) Walleye - 7lbs 7oz (Lake Simcoe) Muskie - 38" (Rice Lake) Pike - 42" (Lake Simcoe) Crappie - 15" (Little Lake) Perch - 14" (Lake Simcoe) Rainbow - 29.5" (Cattaraugus Creek, NY) Brown - 31" (Olcott Creek, NY) Chinook - 34lbs. (Bowmanville Creek)  Type of Fishing: BASS FISHING!! but I love all fishing.  Best Tournament Position: 1st Place x 9 and 32 other top tens.  # of Tournament seasons: 8, with many more to come.  Sponsors: Ghost Baits, Bluewater Optics  Spouse: not married, but have been with Kelli for almost 3 years.  Children: none  Most importantly  Pet peeve: Agreed with fishing etiquette.  Mostly spot poachers, aka non-boaters who are back in your spot the next day with someone else.
